      <item>
        <title>How can I fetch page with slug</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[David]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Yeah, you need to add <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/api-reference-1/wordpress-source#state-source-homepage" rel="nofollow noopener"><code>homepage</code></a> and <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/api-reference-1/wordpress-source#state-source-postspage" rel="nofollow noopener"><code>postsPage</code></a> props in your <code>frontity.settings.js</code> with the slug of each page as values, and it should work.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/how-can-i-fetch-page-with-slug/323/6">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
